Camera Site Description: Mossy bog in black spruce. Started out nice, but turned into garbage with small trees. Found small game trail, no other real options.
Comments and Access Notes: No great instructions, just park on side of raod and bash in. ***BUGS. Checked that it was not a residential area.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood, mainly aspen, thick green understory with lots of shrubs, some mosses. Solid ground, dry. Camera pointed at thick trail but also intersection with another smaller trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road (not very busy) and walk in. Thick interstory but fairly easy to walk.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in aspen dominated mixed stand, shrubby understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack to site, on NE side of highway

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood with conifer, but mainly aspen. Thick with lots of small shrubs inbetween the spaced out trees, little moss, dry soild ground, not many well defined trailsin area but camera is on good defined trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on highway and walk in. Fairly thick shrubs/understory but soild ground. Hwy shoulders were hard but very sloped.

Camera Site Description: Mossy with labrador tea, dry, conifer forest with spruce and larch
Comments and Access Notes: Park at well site and bushwack in.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with horse tail understory, camera along game trail off seismic line.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road near seimic line, walk ~500m on seismic line until game trail on right side.

Camera Site Description: Dry mossy mixed wood (black spruce and some aspen)
Comments and Access Notes: Drive to north end of cell and end at well pad before break in road. Camera directly south in big stand of trees. Cross wet young stand, bring boots. From east side (road does not connect)

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant (black spruce? And larches) forest with some small deciduous shrubs, wet mossy understory with some labrador tea
Comments and Access Notes: Park on SE side of road and bushwack in. Dry spots to walk on with wet deep holes. Camera on game trail but not a very well defined trail.

Camera Site Description: Bog with mossy understory and labrador tea, and black sprue sparse forest along a well defined game trail
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside beside rectangular cutblock feature, walk to back and follow game trail. N side of road.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest (aspen and spruce) with open understory. Fairly dry. Camera pointed at intersection of multiple trails
Comments and Access Notes: Park on main highway a but south of point to avoid bog, no clear path in, but the forest is easy walking so just bash to camera site.

Camera Site Description: Dense understory of labrador tea, black spruce forest. Pretty boggy/mossy, but found a decent game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive to end of road, park in well pad. Duck under pipe to avoid cat tail swamp. Wack in to point, bring boots!

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood with conifers and aspen, hard ground, only some moss, mainly small plant understory, fair amount of old tree fall. Camera pointed at fairly goof trail, small amount of other trails in area.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on highway, walk along the seismic line on North side of highway going north, bushbash in east to site, easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest of aspen, spruce, fir, with understory of rose, moss and bunchberry. Camera along well defined game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park in pull out where seismic line intersects the road. Walk up seismic line for ~150m and enter forest on the right side. Left side has barb wire fence.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with rose, bunchberry, shrub understory. Camera along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road. Walk in on seismic line ~ 150 m and turn onto game trail on the left side.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with rose, bunchberry, shrub understory. Camera along well defined game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road where safe, game trail can be seen from road. Follow to camera. *camera ID not on slate photo.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed forest stand of aspen and conifer, adjacent to inactive wellsite
Comments and Access Notes: Pull into pullout close to site (just NE along road), walk down cutline beside wellpad and turn off on SW side, bushwack to site

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in aspen stand with shrubby understory, adjacent to cutline and active wellpad
Comments and Access Notes: Park at entry to abandoned wellpad on N side of road, follow wellpad to cutline. Folloe cutline until adjacent to site, bushwack in.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in aspen dominant mixed stand, with shrubby understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park at entrance to abandoned well site on south side of road. Walk down cutline/wellsite ~130m and follow game trail into forest on E side of pad.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in aspen dominant mixed forest stand, shrubby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at entrance to abandoned well site, follow site until adjacent to point and bushwack in

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with shrubby understory. Camera along well-defined game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road where safe, follow old road/seismic line (overgrown) for ~150m to game trail on right side.

Camera Site Description: Mossy solid ground with rose bushes, lots of game trails nearby, lots of deadfall, camera pointed at game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Parked on well pad/gas station and bush bashed in, fairly easy walking, lots of game trails.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in deciduous aspen forest, shrubby sparse understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside at old road/truck trail, follow road and bushwack to camera once parallel

Camera Site Description: Pretty open spruce patch with squishy mossy and labrador tea. Camera at junction of several game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive to end at road and reach old pad used for storage? No clear entry into forest, just pray and bush bash. Boots recommended.

Camera Site Description: Mixed black spruce and labrador tea. Series of "tiny" game trails, tried to get camera at intersection.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad just South of cell 60, to east of camera. Not a clear path in, but a dryish bush wack. Camera is near where trees get small and labrador tea is abundant.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood forest at the end of an old road. Camera site placed before the woods get too thick of an understory. Facing eat at downed tree.
Comments and Access Notes: Convenient pull out off western site of the cell. Walk down old road, past brunt old jeep, then hard right into forest.

Camera Site Description: Mainly deciduous, thick with branchy shrubs and birch, wet uneven grassy ground, some trails but not very well defined, camera is placed on birch tree pointed at trail, lure went on branchy shrubs.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and walk in, satellite photos show cut line/seismic line, but not very over grown.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with mossy/grassy understory, rose and bunchberry. Camera along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road or near well pad and bushwack in ~200 to game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with moss, rose, shrubby understory. Camera along well defined game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road in safe area. Camera is ~150 m off road along game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest site with moss, bunchberry and rose understory. Camera along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road in a safe pullout near seismic line that intersects with road, bushwack in ~150 m.

Camera Site Description: Solid mossy ground right at camera site with mixed forest (multiple species of conifer as well as aspen and birch), but near site is thick mossy boggy terrain with conifer trees, lots of labrador tea nearby but not right at site.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and walk straight north from the NW corner of the pad. Walk thru conifer moss bog to get to a grove with large pine trees, camera is on game trail.

Camera Site Description: Dryish labrador tea bog with Black spruce. Shockingly high number of game trails compared to similar habitats we have seen.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and walk into forest on south side. You will eventually hit game trails, but otherwise easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Solid ground moss understory, some shrubs, mainly conifers (large) and some aspens nearby. Two game trails intersect infront of camera.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on side of road and walk in, easy walking for most part.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed forest stand (roughly equal aspen and conifer trees) mossy ground with shrubby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at bridge (safe pullout), walk ~500m southward on road, bushwack to site once roughly perpendicular. Should be able to find a game trail.

Camera Site Description: Very open site, conifer with mainly pine, moss and lichen forest floor, few shrubs except around perimeter of open pot, slight slope to west, camera pointed towards defined game trail
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in. Shrubs and trees thick at first then there is a very open forest patch, follow game trail to camera.

Camera Site Description: Thick mossy understory with labrador tea, mainly conifer forest at site. Only aspens are closer to well pad.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and bush bash into site accessed from SE corner of well pad and bush bash in SE direction.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood with conifer and aspen, green mossy understory, some shrubs but not very thick, solid ground, dry, camera along established game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and walk in, in NE direction, easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, open understory. Lots of trails around camera site.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive to well pad and venture North into old clearing. Thick at first but opens up into open understory. No clear trail until you reach the camera.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with mossy understory, labrador tea, deadfall. Camera along faint game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park alonf road and follow seismic line approx. ~ 150m. Faint game trail on left side of seismic line.

Camera Site Description: Camera facing down game trail in mixed tree stand (largely conifer with some aspen, adjacent to a very seismic line). Mossy understory with sparse veg.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at oull out beside bridge, walk N 500m from bridge northward on road until approx parallel with site coordinates, bushwack in. Do not cross seismic line - overgrown shite.

Camera Site Description: Open forest with big Black spruce. Many active game trails, camera pointed down trail with lure tree to left. Intersection of trails at lure tree!
Comments and Access Notes: Park just south of cell along a GIANT pond with beaver lodge. Easy walk along pond, then cut into forest. See datasheet for diagra.

Camera Site Description: Lovely aspen site, big trees with somewhat thick understory. Camera on well defined trail
Comments and Access Notes: Access from outside of cell on south east corner. Road was quite wet so we parked at end and walked in. Walk along olf road until perpendicular to camera, hard left and get on in there.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant stand with mossy understory, with horsetail and thorny shrubs. Camera pointing down well defined game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and follow seismic trail from road. Hard to see, may have to bushwack to find trail.

Camera Site Description: Solid ground with moss and other plants as understory, mixed wood with pine, other conifers, and aspen. Near boggy area to North that is lower in elevation.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad, walk through bog to aspen mixed forest.

Camera Site Description: Mossy solid ground, mixed wood (conifer and aspen)
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in, easy walking. Road is very busy, be careful!

Camera Site Description: Open seismic line with mossy and labrador tea. Interior forest trees small and garbage seismic line game trail was the best so we set it up and lured fallen tree.
Comments and Access Notes: Very clear seismic line, walk down well defined game trail on line, camera is on left pointed at fallen tree.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed forest stand, predominantly aspen, location has small shrub understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack to site

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest , mostly older aspen. Understory of rose, bunchberry and grasses. Along game trail
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road and follow seismic line ~500m, turn right onto intersecting seismic line and follow for ~200m, game trail on left side.

Camera Site Description: Mossy mixed forest. Camera on tree surrounded by wet moss, pointing down trail NE.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive to well pad, park on left. Follow game trail on seismic line, veer into forest following smaller trail on right, Bring BOOTS.

Camera Site Description: Mossy bog, conifer forest, grass and labrador tea and smalll birch understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad and walk through bog until you get to taller trees. Buggy!

Camera Site Description: Fairly dry mossy solid ground, mixed wood aspen and conifer, near large cut line, nice trails in area, camera pointing at 2 trails intersecting.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in, walk past large cut line, then follow game trail to camera.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, conifer and aspen with shruby understory, roses and moss. Some game trails, few well-defined.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack to site. Camera on slightly learning tree along game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood, solid mossy understory with small amount of labrador tea and shrubs. East of cutline.
Comments and Access Notes: Park in oullout on N side of road. Walk down cutline in S direction, bushwack ~20m on E side of cutline. Solid ground, easy walk.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood, ~60:40 conifer aspen, solid dry ground with moss, plants and lots of rose shrubs. Camera is pointed down a trail and at intersection of another trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in North. Some rose shrubs and downfall but fairly easy walking. Found some bear poop and evil grouse.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with mossy understory, some shrubs. Lots of game trails, bear scat at camera site.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack ~120m to camera site. Along well defined game trail.

Camera Site Description: Dry ish ground with moss and labrador tea understory, conifer forest, next to cutline (winter snowmibile road?). A weather station is also in the cell.
Comments and Access Notes: Land in clearing south west of point, walk North along cut line, then East into forest along game trail to find camera. * Slate time wrong. Time may be off @ this site, might be out in 12h time.

Camera Site Description: Very nice mossy spruce area. Good trails all around.
Comments and Access Notes: Land in old river bed looking thing at south west corner of cell. Climb hill and walk in until nice open mossy forest.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood, solid dry ground with moss and rose shrub understory, lots of deadfalll, near cutline that was for an abandonned pipeline (there are signs).
Comments and Access Notes: Land in large cutblock near SW portion of cell, walk to western cutline a few meters, camera is south of that cutline along a trail.

Camera Site Description: Dry ground with moss, lichen, and labrador tea, conifer forest (black spruce), camera along cutline, and nearby a large cut block
Comments and Access Notes: Land in large cutblock to East or NE of point, walk along cutlines to find camera.

Camera Site Description: Very thick spruce area with mossy bottom. No clear defined trail but we were able to find a bit of a clearing in the trees. Some miminal animal sign.
Comments and Access Notes: From landing area you have to walk across a soft open area north ish. No clear entry into forest unfortunately.

Camera Site Description: On game trail at intersection of 2 high use linear features in mixed wood forest. Lure tree is an already active bear rub tree.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - land at + of linear features.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed conifer stand with mossy understory that has sparse labrador tea site is immediately in transition from wet to dry.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - land in abandoned wellsite, hike into bush on SW side, follow game trail to site. No photos.

Camera Site Description: Mixed stand, mossy bottom, deadfall. Near river.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - E side of river, walk into forest ~30m

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant forest with mossy bottom, some shrubs (labrador tea, rose). Near river.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - SW side of river, walk into forest on game trail, trail will turn and run parallel to river heading SE. Well-defined game trail.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail adjacent to open bog. Black spruce forest with wet mossy understory and sparse labrador tea and lichen.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - land in open bog, walk to E side to camera.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant forest, mossy/shrubby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Land on seismic line, walk up line and game trail in on left (South)

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest next to bog.
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - enter forest and bushwack to site

Camera Site Description: Mossy ground, mixed forest. Lots of squirrel trails but camera is pointed along a trail that appears wider then a squirrel trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in (NE direction from road). SW side of road was completely flooded when we first looked at the cell.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest (pine, aspen, fir) with mossy, labrador tea, shruby understory. Many well defined game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park in pullout near pond. Bushwack for ~120m, game trail can be seen/followed to camera site.

Camera Site Description: Conifer forest with spongy moss, good trails, some labrador tea.
Comments and Access Notes: Land on SE edge of boggy area, slightly wet, walk in. Lots of trails, easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Game trail off high use seismic line in black spruce bog with mossy understory with lichen and labrador tea.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line on W side of road to site.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, mainly conifer (larches, pines and spruce), mosst ground, adjacent to cutline. Lots of squirrel trails, camera is pointed along wider, suspected large game trail. Close to spongy-labrador tea black spruce area.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in cutline in N direction when perpendicular to point. Walk in E to camera. Camera is along a game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mossy solid ground, mixed forest, fairly open, lots of deadfall, lots of shrubs and plants.
Comments and Access Notes: Land in grassy area east of creek, follow game trail into woods east to camera.

Camera Site Description: Game trail in mixed forest stand with sparse understory of conifer saplings and horsetail, lots of bear sign. Forest path adjacent to cutblock.
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter acccess - forest patch on N side of cutblock

Camera Site Description: In a conifer stand, mossy groundcover, rather dense understory. Many small game trails, lack of obvious large game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, bushwack ~150m in.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest on a seismic line. Mossy understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk up seismic line ~ 350 m (diagonal) camera attached to conifer tree.

Camera Site Description: Faint game trail coming out of a conifer dominant mixed wood stand, onto high use seismic line. Mossy ground with fireweed and labrador tea.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk down seismic line on N side of road to site.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, mostly conifer, mossy understory, some shrubs. Good game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Near edge of wetland/bog area. Follow game trail in around NW part of bog.

Camera Site Description: Along a game trail leading from a mixed forest stand (aspen dominant with sparse fireweed understory) to open wetland area.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside beside cutblock on S side of road, walk to W-edge of feature and bushwack to site.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, mostly conifer. Mossy/grassy understory. Well-defined game trails. Camera is just outside cell 56 (nowhere to land)
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Land is grassy bog area and walk into forest ~50 m to the camera site. BOOTS!! VERY WET!

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with mossy ground. Varying tree sizes. Adjacent to cutline.
Comments and Access Notes: Land in grassy area on east side, walk east down cutline then follow game trail to camera.

Camera Site Description: Along a game trail that comes off a seismic line at forest-bog interface into mixed stand, conifer dominant with mossy, labrador tea understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and walk down seismic line that borders forest /bog interface on E side of road for ~150m, then enter game trail into forest to site.

Camera Site Description: In a spruce patch next to bog, grassy ground cover.
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - follow trail from bog

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest about 10 m from a seismic line. Attached to an aspen.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk along seismic line (past the "x" intersection), game trail is on the right.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest on a aspen tree. Next to a lake.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk on edge of lake (~200m) to older foreset at the back of the lake.

Camera Site Description: Mossy ground, mixed wood but mostly conifer, some willow shrubs, adjacent to open/willow shrub area.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Land in south end of open grassy area south of a creek, follow game trail to camera.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest, little ground cover
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - walk on game trail to site

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest next to beaver pond
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - tree might be cut down by beavers by next year.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant forest, mossy bottom with labrador tea and grasses.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Walk down seismic line near gas station/pump. Camera on E side.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest, little ground cover
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access, in mixed forest

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest next to a river
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - land in river (NW side) and walk to site

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest next to slope leading down to river.
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - walk into mixed stand adjacent to river.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant forest, mossy bottom near bog. Labrador tea and shrubs.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Follow game trail a few meters into forest.

Camera Site Description: In a black spruce bog, edge of clearing on game trail
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - camera is located on the edge of the clearing

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest near wetland/river. Conifer with aspen, shruby bottom.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Faint game trail a few meters from edge of clearing.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest off the intersection of two seismic lines
Comments and Access Notes: Helicopter access - follow seismic line to site

Camera Site Description: Along a game trail in mixed stand, moss and labrador tea understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access beside a river bed.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant, mossy bottom.
Comments and Access Notes: Heli access - Follow seismic line to game trail on right side. Few meters off seismic line.

Camera Site Description: Dry ground, some moss, grass and plants and shrubs. Mixed forest, fairly open spot, nearby beaver dam. Also found ungulate poop.
Comments and Access Notes: Land on open patch NE of little river and beaver dam. Walk in.

Camera Site Description: Mossy trail on edge of beaver pond clearing
Comments and Access Notes: Walk to point, not far from clearing

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood, mainly conifer, adjacent to open grassy patch, soild ground with moss and plants
Comments and Access Notes: Land in North end of grassy patch and walk in, on edge of forest.

Camera Site Description: High use seismic line in boggy area. Black spruce + tamarack canopy, moss/labrador tea ground cover.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line on S side of road for ~550 m to site

Camera Site Description: In a conifer forest at the intersection of seismic lines, moss and lavender tea ground cover.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk ~200m up seismic line.

Camera Site Description: In black spruce canopy, moss and lavender tea understory, on seismic line.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk through well pad to seismic line and follow to site (~200 m).

Camera Site Description: On a seismic line in a mixed forest, little ground cover.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk ~100m down seismic line (on west side of road), follow seismic lines to site. *requires suncor escort through aerodome gate, 2023=Dustin*

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood stand w/ moss and plant understory, lots of variation in tree height and type of forests around camera, very small open meadow nearby.
Comments and Access Notes: Worker said lots of hunters in area, we also saw a discarded moose cargass nearby to wear high vis. Park on road and walk in south. If parking on corner get right off road, was solid enough when we parked. Camera is close to the "no-go" zone, but not within in.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, quite open, solid dry ground, lots of shrubs and plants in understory. Lots of deadfall, camera is along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on main road and walk in SE. Alternatively, park on road headed to Kearl compensation lake infront of the gate, then walk along road and walk in. There MAY be cameras at this gate. Someone was waiting for us when we parked infron of this gate, and just politely asked what we were doing. Access to the compensation late was prohibited at the time. Ecosite unknown because new cell after site selection.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, very variable tree height, clump of labrador tea near camera, lots of shrubs, some moss and plants, lots of downfall.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and bushwack in (SE from road). We saw a wold @ this site! Keep your eyes peeled. Multiple people warned us about lots of bears in the area as well. Don’t forget bear spray. Ecosite unknown because new cell after site selection.

Camera Site Description: Shrubby birch forest, mostly small trees with some areas of open understory. Animal sign and defined trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive up road nea camera ~200m to open area near weather station with electric fence. Bushwack ~110 meters to camera site. Along well-defined game trail. Ecosite unknown because new cell after site selection.

Camera Site Description: Game trail on seismic line in black spruce forest moss + labrador tea understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow big seismic line on N side of road, turn W onto smaller line to site.

Camera Site Description: On a game trail on a high use seismic line in black spruce conifer forest - mossy ground w/ labrador tea.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line on W side of road to site (will pass through 2 well pads) *requires suncor escort through aerodome gate, 2023=Dustin Wells*

Camera Site Description: Game trail on high use seismic line - black spruce forest w/ mossy ground w/ lichen + labrador tea
Comments and Access Notes: *Requires suncor escort through aerodome gate, 2023=Dustin Wells* Park roadside beside air strip, follow seismic line on W side of road to site.

Camera Site Description: Conifer stand (black spruce?) with spongy mossy ground, lots of labrador tea. Camera is in open spot, pointing @ a log. Squirrel activity in area, as well as large mammal (moose tracks)
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and bushwack in. Lots of downfall @ first, but gets slightly better. Roses!

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with shrubby understory, labrador tea, rose, blueberry. Well defined trails and animal signs.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and follow cutline for ~200m untill intersection, go left at intersection, follow old road(?) / game trail to camera site. Along well-defined game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest stand, shruby understory with lots of deadfall. Surrounded by small conifer trees, lots of large aspens.
Comments and Access Notes: Long, slightly overgrown road, driveable but need to go very slow. About ~30 minutes one way. Road will pass then loop back left to the stand of large trees. Follow game trail in, camera on large aspen. Ecosite unknown because new cell after site selection.

Camera Site Description: Open meadow surrounded by small aspens. Understory of bearberry, lichens, grass. Camera on edge of open area on aspen.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside. Walk through young aspens to open meadow. Walk towards back of open area. Camera on SW side of meadow. Facing downed branch along faint game trail.

Camera Site Description: Seismic line in black spruce/tamarack forest, mossy/labrador tea ground cover
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line ~150 m to site.

Camera Site Description: In a black spruce forest with moss and labrador tea understory. On a seismic line.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line ~200m to site.

Camera Site Description: Open area where 2 seismic lines meet w/ intersecting game trails, black spruce and tamarack canopy, w/ moss, horsetail, and labrador tea understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic lines on W side of road.

Camera Site Description: Seismic line w/ game trail in black spruce stand, moss/lichen/labrador tea ground cover
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow seismic line on S-side of road to site

Camera Site Description: Game trail in old growth jackpine stand w/lichen + labrador tea understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside in large open area, enter forest near far SE corner ~150 m to site.

Camera Site Description: Trail off a seismic line in black spruce forest w/ moss + labrador tea understory
Comments and Access Notes: Take small side road on W-side of main road, park at corner, follow large cutline heading W and turn down a seismic line to site.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest at edge of open area. Mostly young trees and shrubs. Grassy/shruby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at old road with gate, walk up (quick walk) road ~500 m to the rectangular open area. Camera is on game trail in West corner of open area down a slight slope.

Camera Site Description: Conifer forest, lots of shrubs, dry solid ground w/ low plants, adjacent to old cutline w/very well defined game trail, camera is on another game trail that shoots off of main one.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive down small road on S side of main road and park at sandy area where it intersects with old cutline running NE-SE. Walk along overgrown cutline in SW direction and follow trail offshoot to camera. Very overgrown, have to duck LOL.

Camera Site Description: Solid dry ground w/ some moss, plants, and shrubs, camera in pine stand adjacent to aspen stand, and young pine stand (old clearcut?) very faint game trail, fairlyopen area.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on side of road and walk in, easy walking. Camera is @ end of the large pine stand.

Camera Site Description: Open dry area with spaced out tall pines mixed in with short young pines, solid dry ground w/ lichen + bearberry, evidence of a past forest fire. Adjacent to a clearcut.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in N (NW), walk through small pines, past clearcut, to larger stand. Camera is in the larger pine stand. Some bear shit in area.

Camera Site Description: Open site w/ tall trees, mostly pine but some aspen nearby. Some shrubs, low plants, and moss in understory. ~50m N of site is old butblock w/ baby pines. Tracks, bear poop, and wolf? poop in area
Comments and Access Notes: Drive down road south of main road that points in SE direction, turn down next road to right the points in SW direction. Drive till you can’t then walk to site. Easy walking, lots of bear poop!

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood stand w/ pine and aspen, surrounded by small pines. Some shrubs and blueberries and bearberries in understory. Fairly open site. Some trails + tracks in area, camera is placed on suspected trail intersection.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on main road and walk in. Easy walking. Camera is in pine stand with larger trees.

Camera Site Description: Pine forest with open understory, shrubs, bearberry, blueberry. Some defined trails and bear scat.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack (easy walking) ~170 m to camera site, near back of large pine tree area.

Camera Site Description: Open jackpine stand in area of dense young pine trees. Bearberry understory, very open. Very faint game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park in open area on right after entering road off main road. Walk to back past the monitoring station towards clump of large trees. Camera long faint trail.

Camera Site Description: Pine forest with open understory, some shrubs (blueberry) and bearberry. Few defined game trails
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk ~200m back to camera site, past small aspen stand.

Camera Site Description: Game trail in old growth conifer stand w/ sparse blueberry understory. Adjacent to young regenerating pine stand.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive down low-use wellpad access road on N side of main road ~1 km to wellpad. Park @ wellpad, continue on road by foot until at forest stand. Follow game trail to site.

Camera Site Description: Pine dominant forest (lodgepole?), mostly open understory with shrubs, roses, blueberry, lots of deadfall. Some faint game trails + bearscat nearby
Comments and Access Notes: Park near forest patch and bushwack in ~ 100m. Camera on game trail.

Camera Site Description: An island of older conifer trees in a sea of tiny trees. No game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, bushwack through tiny trees ~120m. Find island.

Camera Site Description: Fir forest, open understory with some bearberry, blueberry, shrubs. No well-defined trails in the area, very little animal sign.
Comments and Access Notes: Turn south on road in middle of cell. Park near cleaing for powerlines. Walk into forest ~150 m past sandy patch. No good game trails

Camera Site Description: Camera is in pine stand of older tres, looks to be burned once but some larger trees surviving. Small pines ~ 5-10 ft surrounding the larger pine tree stand that the camera is in. Open forest floor with some low plants. Powerlines nearby. Sandy ground.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road (sandy, make sure shoulder is stable), walk in south of road, cross powerlines, walk through thick small pines till you reach the larger tree pine stand. No defined game trail but camera was placed along moose tracks.

Camera Site Description: Small clump of conifer in area of regrowth. Labrador tea, blueberry, shrubs. Lots of deadfall, faint game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Follow road into cell as far as possible, then follow (walk along) over grown road. Road is sandy with some debris but driveable. Follow game trail to site ~100m from overgorwn road.

Camera Site Description: Along a faint game trail in a mixed forest stand, aspen dominant, young aspen + blueberry understory. Camera on a conifer adjacent to cutblock + old burn.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk through old burn and cutblock ~500m to small mixed stand.

Camera Site Description: In a thin strip of conifer forest, new growth on either side.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk up strip of old growth forest ~300m.

Camera Site Description: In a mixed forest stand surrounded by burn. On a conifer tree.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk through dense growth ~200m

Camera Site Description: Game trail at edge of small aspen-dominated mixed stand, ~300m away from old truck trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and walk into old truck trail, follow until adjacent to site location.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest stand w/few mature trees (<10), young aspen + labrador tea understory, in a depression feature
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow linear feature on S side of road for ~350m (start is bushwacking but opens up), follow faint game trail to site.

Camera Site Description: On edge of older conifer stand beside conifer stand with younger growth.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, follow edge of older pine stand to near the back of the stand for about 150m.

Camera Site Description: Fir forest, open understory with some blueberries, bearberries, lots of deadfall. Few well-defined game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Turn onto road that goes north through the cell. Road is hilly but driveable. Drive near cell and walk into forest to camera site, few good game trails in area.

Camera Site Description: Open pine forests w/ lots of deadfall. Mossy/lichen forest floor, no plants or shrubs, camera is on suspected trail (tracks, and bark removed from logs)
Comments and Access Notes: Turn down little road (south of main road) and park at end (only a short road). Walk in rest of way, easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Open pine forest, no plants or shrubs in understory. Dry, some sand, evidence of burn at some point. Logging nearby (clearcut with stacked loggs). Evidence of large animals moving nearby (tracks and bark scraped off downed trees) but not well defined trail. Definitely used by squirrels!
Comments and Access Notes: If possible, turn down small road on south side of main road and immediately turn right. Drive down a short ways then walk in. Camera is in stand past a clearcut area.

Camera Site Description: In a boggy conifer forest next to a burn. Prominent game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, walk through burn 300m to edge of conifer forest bog

Camera Site Description: Game trail in conifer stand surrounded by young burn regrowth. Understory is blueberry and small, young conifer.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside at old road on N side of road. Follow until first tree stand on E side of old road.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in small aspen (<10 big trees) stand surrounded by burn, ground is regenerating aspen/pine remnants of moose kill @ site.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive down old road on N-side of main road for ~ 250 m, then hike through burn to site.

Camera Site Description: Pine stand surrounding lake. Larger pine trees cuffer the lake (where the camera is), and smaller pines surround the rest of the area. Lots of shrubs + plants (blueberries, bearberries, alder shrubs?). Some deciduous trees in area. Camera on ridge of lake, slopes down W
Comments and Access Notes: Park close to lake on sandy intersection of roads and walk in, camera is on SE corner of second lake (first lake is more of a bog).

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, spruce and aspen, camera is near seismic line. Understory fairly open.
Comments and Access Notes: Park near road intersection where seismic line meets road. Walk ~ 140 m up the road and enter forest near camera location on left hand side.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest (aspen and spruce) with shruby/open understory. Camera along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside near seismic line (very overgrown). Bushwack ~115 m parallel to seismic line.

Camera Site Description: Quite dense aspen with lots of deadfall. Found little clearing with a decent trail going through. Burnt stump in frame, area must have burned somewhat recently?
Comments and Access Notes: Park on rad and prepare for a very thick bushwack. Sorry about that…

Camera Site Description: *Very* open mixed wood, plenty of trails around, buggy
Comments and Access Notes: Easy walk in on old cutline, turn left into forest, enjoy leisurly walk to camera

Camera Site Description: Spruce dominated stand with mossy understory. Lots of game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road near the bend and seismic line (very overgrown). Bushwack in ~100m from road.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, conifer dominant. Mossy understory, lots of deadfall, some shrubs. Camera along game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park near corner of road, bushwack in ~ 150m to camera.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest on slight slope. Camera pointed at nice intersection of trails. LOTS of beaver activity here, expect this to be a bangin beaver site. (Drawing of a beaver)
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and there is an old looking cut with trees, you can walk in easy and then start going downhill. No clear trail to follow in, wack to point.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with aspen and spruce, fairly open understory. Camera along game trail
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside (pullout near where seismic line meets road). Seismic line not visible from road, follow and find game trail ~ 150 m from road.

Camera Site Description: Predominantly aspen stand with steep slope south of camera. No well-defined game trails. Shrubby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at road to small active well pad. Walk to back of well pad and bushwack ~120 m to camera.

Camera Site Description: Open mixed forest adjacent to wetland. Flat spot, but near areas of slope.
Comments and Access Notes: You can park on the side of the main road and walk southish down an old truck road. Stop before you hit the "no dumping" sign, take a left, and enjoy the easy walk in.

Camera Site Description: Predominantly spruce forest with mossy and horsetail understory. Many well-defined game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park at deccomissioned well pad and walk to back, follow game trail for ~100m.

Camera Site Description: Game trail heading NE from large cutline, young aspen conifer trees, sparse shrubby understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside at S-bound cutline before heading NE into forest along edge.

Camera Site Description: Along a game trail that follows the edge of a conifer stand, running parallel w/old road. Mossy forest floor and young conifer/aspen on periphery
Comments and Access Notes: Drive ~200m down abandoned road on W side at main road. Walk from car to side, no need to go into forest.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in a conifer stand w/ dry mossy understory
Comments and Access Notes: Drive down abandoned road, park at abandoned wellpad and follow game trail to site on E side of wellpad

Camera Site Description: Mossy understory in sprucy forest. Looks like nearly decommissioned road. Lots of beaver activity in area.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road, very clear cutline of sorts, potentially decommissioned road? Bit of an ankle breaker walk so be careful. But walk ~300m and then take a left into forest when perpendicular with GPS point. (Stop to admire beaver lodge on left before turning in)

Camera Site Description: Somewhat thick wood, mix of aspen, birch, and conifers, lots of old deadfall, green/mossy solid forest floor, covered with leaves so was somewhat dificult to see game trail. Camera is in open patch on suspected trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on side of road and walk in, easy walking, only really thick at first. Road is not actively used by the looks of it, but safe to drive on as of this season.

Camera Site Description: Thick yound aspen, looks like very old burn site, solid dry ground with few plants in understory, mainly small trees + shrubs, some conifers. Camera is placed along suspected game trail (leaves make trails obscured). Sloping down to E
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road or nose into green area on S side of road, walk into cleared patch and walk/bushwack up the hill and in to find camera. Camera is on aspen tree.

Camera Site Description: Very thick and rosey thorn bush site. Camera on a slight slope pointing into a bit of a clearing, somewhat perpendicular to a trail. Not a lot of options here…
Comments and Access Notes: Drive onto old abandoned well pad, and bushwack off back end. Be warned, it is extreamly rosey + thorny. You will get stabbed.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, aspen and spruce with clear understory near camera. Surrounding camera understory is shrubby.
Comments and Access Notes: Park along road near camera.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed stand w/ dominant aspen. Sparsley shrubby understory.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive up abandoned road ~175m, park and bushwack to site.

Camera Site Description: Area is previously burnt, camera located in small stand of spruce with spongy moss. Much deadfall, few signs of wildlife, but pretty representitive of area.
Comments and Access Notes: Very good old road you can walk down, probably don’t drive this, seems too old. Oncec you are perpendicular with point, turn left and grab camera in stand of trees.

Camera Site Description: Located in aspen stand with some conifers. At time of setup ground was covered in leaves making it difficult to locate game trails, but we think camera is along a trail. Some shrubs, solid ground, green plant ground w/ some moss
Comments and Access Notes: Park on old well pad and walk in, in SE direction. Fairly easy walking.

Camera Site Description: Spruce/mossy area, pretty low wildlife use, only found a few trails. No great cam/lure tree combo, so dragged a dead tree infront of camera and lured it on sparse trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Good parking on some sort of pad. Walk down transmission line ~100m, turn right into forest.

Camera Site Description: Along a game trail on a possible old seismic line, mixed forest stand w/ mossy understory; right before a hill descent.
Comments and Access Notes: Drive up road until adjacent with site, bushwack from east side of road.

Camera Site Description: Dry mossy ground, mix of conifers and deciduous, adjacent to open patch (looks natural, not human caused), lots of deadfall + shrubs nearby
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and bushwack in, try and find access through the deadfall, very thick! May have to park on straight stretch then walk for parking safety. Camera is right next to open-ish line (looks like old cutblock but seems natural).

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with pruce and aspen, shrubby understory with dense areas. Well defined game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park near seismic line (very overgrown, don’t follow) at corner of road. Bushwack ~120 m in to camera.

Camera Site Description: Game trail in mixed orest stand dominated by aspen, sparse shrubby understory
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside, bushwack on N side of road to site

Camera Site Description: Immediately adjacent to old seizmic line, very over grown. Uneven ground with slopes near camera but camera is on fairly flat spot. Mixed wood with conifers but primarily aspen. Lots of leaves on ground but camera is on game trail, many shrubs nearby, solid ground.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in on old seizmic line or beside it. Be vareful if parking on corner, at the time of setup there was a large pull-off right on the corner that was solid and safe.

Camera Site Description: Solid ground, adjacent to cut line, aspen + pine trees, some shrubs, quite dry, thick wood with small tree, possible old wildfire area, small slope to NE
Comments and Access Notes: Park on well pad (active @ time) and walk in via cutline, camera ~ 12 m in on left.

Camera Site Description: Mixed wood (conifer+aspen/birch), lots of shrubs, horsetail, labrador tea in understory, solid dry-ish ground, fairly uneven ground but camera site fairly flat. Old hunting stand in tree ~25 m away. Very good game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on side of road and walk in through old road and old well pad, then walk into bush and find the well defined trail.

Camera Site Description: Along game trail in mixed forest stand, mossy understory. Adjacent to conifer dry bog.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack in. It sucks, sorry.

Camera Site Description: Along faint game trail in mixed wood stand dominated by aspen, understory is sparse
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside by cutline on W side of road, follow cutline/bushwack

Camera Site Description: Spongy moss w/ some labrador tea @ site. To west is bog, to east is solid ground (no moss) mixed wood. Right @ site is mixed wood, some shrubs. Not very good trails, but camera is on small trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in West, easy walk! Some deadfall.

Camera Site Description: On game trail in mixed forest stand dominated by conifers, sparse sapling understory and mossy ground.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside @ cutline on N side of road, follow until parallel w/ site (or follow in forest)

Camera Site Description: Mossy understory in mixed wood, adjacent to a more open patch consisting of shrubs. Camera is on a conifer.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and bushack in (east side of road). Medium bushwack.  ***Camera may not work well, looking at gear inventory apparently this particular camera does not hold a charge, but was not sent away for fixing***

Camera Site Description: Mixed, conifer and aspen (50-50 split), lots of deadfall, ~20 m from cutline along game trail. Solid ground with moss and other plants, lots of leaves on ground @ time of setup
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in along cutline. Road to access site had some vegetation covering it at time of setup, but had solid ground and was safe to drive on. Seizmic line was easy walking

Camera Site Description: Along game trail through an open mixed forest stand w/ mossy ground and sparse fireweed
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack to site (S side of road). Perhaps one of the best in the northern part of this LU!!

Camera Site Description: Lots of squirrel/small mammal trails but few large trails; camera is on largest trail in nearby area. Mossy understory in mixed forest. Ground fairly solid and dry. Patch of sphagnum moss + labrador tea nearby but not directly at camera site.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk in straight North.

Camera Site Description: Flat, solid, dry ground w/ moss and some small plants, some rose shrubs in understory. Mixed wood with conifers and deciduous (majority conifer). Some trails but not well defined, camera on trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on clearing @ T-intersection of 2 roads and bushbash in. Some roses but fairly easy walk. Camera is on a conifer pointed @ a very large conifer. (No site photos were taken)

Camera Site Description: Down a game trail on a slope in mixed stand dominated by old growth conifer w/ thick rose understory. Looks like it may have been logged many years ago.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and endure a bushwack from hell to site on E side of road.

Camera Site Description: On a game trail in an old mixed stand w/ mossy understory. Little animal sign in forest.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack from E side of road.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, open floor. Camera faces a fallen tree
Comments and Access Notes: Park on main road and walk down old truck road until perpendicular with point. Sharp left into forest. Boggy at first, then opens up. Continue for ~300m. Alternate: to skip boggy area, go straight to point from road.

Camera Site Description: Conifer dominant stand with mossy understory. Lots of game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack ~130 m to camera site. On well-defined game trail.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest with mossy bottom, camera pointed straight down game trail.
Comments and Access Notes: Park on road and walk to site.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest, conifer and aspen with moss and labrador tea understory. Lots of well-defined game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park near open field and walk to back. Bushwack ~80m from back of field to camera. Camera along well-defined game trail. On aspen facing two aspen.

Camera Site Description: Open mixed forest, bit of a slope pointed up towards a clearing.
Comments and Access Notes: No good instructions, just bushwack to camera.

Camera Site Description: Pretty open mixed wood forest. Camera points west down trail into little clearing. Adjacent to old cutline?
Comments and Access Notes: If driving north, somewhat cryptic cutline on left. You may be tempted to talk it, but beware the thick roses. Better to just skirt the line through the forest, but you do you.

Camera Site Description: Mixed forest (aspen + spruce) with mostly open understory. Labrador tea, moss and shrub understory. Many good game trails.
Comments and Access Notes: Park roadside and bushwack ~120 m to camera. Along well-defined game trail.

Camera Site Description: Ok… So site access was painful, so we had little options. Camera is located on edge of an old burn, and all we could find was a semi-open area with lots of fallen trees. Some tiny trails nearby, but not a banger site. Representative of the cell though!
Comments and Access Notes: Park south of bridge on edge of old burn/cutblock? You can skirt the dense stuff until you are straight south of camera, and then walk downhill into camera. Sorry.

Camera Site Description: Open mixed forest with mossy understory. Some shrubs and labrador tea. Nice game trails! On edge of ridge but camera site is flat
Comments and Access Notes: Park near overgrown road (nice walking), stay left at fork. Enter game trail/overgrown ATV trail on left side. Follow for ~ 100m to camera site. Well-defined game trail.
